==English==
===Noun===
#A form of [[energy]], caused by the behavior of [[electron]]s and [[proton]]s.
#A fundamental property of matter, appearing in [[negative]] and [[positive]] kinds.
#The flow of [[charge]] carriers within a [[conductor]].
#A class of physical phenomena
#A field a physical science
#:'''Quotations'''
#:*'''1646''' .... Sir Thomas Browne, in ''...'' (First known English usage)
#:*'''02.IX.2000''' Householders could one day be producing as much '''electricity''' as all the country's nuclear power stations combined, thanks to the revolutionary application of a device developed in the early 19th century. - ''[http://www.guardian.co.uk/renewable/Story/0,2763,363461,00.html James Meek, The Guardian]'' (2000)

